data.description: Did you say you wanted land and a beautiful house? Look no further! As if lifted from a storybook, a white picket fence frames this beautiful Charleston style home that sits on a 2 acre corner lot! Your dream awaits you!Boasting 2 acres of cleared land completely ready for your animals, 3 bedrooms and 2.5 baths, this beauty offers so many unique features, add-ons, and updates that the sellers have done! This Southern sanctuary, where every detail reflects a life of comfort, elegance, and the true spirit of Southern living. Step into the epitome of Southern charm with this exquisite Charleston-style home with double porches, metal roof, 5-car garage plus two car carport, this property seamlessly blends elegance with functionality, making it an entertainer'sparadise. This property is ready for immediate farm life with barns and fencing. The home and property has hosted many events, weddings, and parties. Your new home could be an income generator for you and possibly pay the mortgage for you.  Additional features include a custom built long outdoor table and deck great for oyster roasts and entertaining! Outdoor kitchen with hog cooker. LED outdoor string lights set the mood for evening entertainment. This home literally has it all. Make sure you ask to see the features page with all of the add-ons and updates.   This timeless beauty was built in 2008. Inside, revel in the open floor plan adorned with custom cabinets, granite countertops, hardwood floors, and a warm propane fireplace. There are so many windows throughout the home allowing lots of natural light to fill each room. On the second floor you will find the owner suite, a sanctuary of luxury, featuring a tray ceiling, double doors opening to an outdoor porch for starlit nights and morning coffees, a spacious walk-in closet, and a double-sized shower for ultimate indulgence. There are two additional good size bedrooms and another full size bathroom on the second floor. Escape to the tranquility of the countryside without sacrificing modern convenience.  The current owners have poured so much love into this home and property during their ownership.  Adding a 24'x41' insulated 4 car garage on concrete foundation.  Added 4,500 sf concrete driveway (rear). Rear driveway used to be old gravel. They replaced the culvert, as well. A 12'x20' structure next to the shop/carport was added- fully insulated and finished office with electricity (climate controlled space with window a/c and space heater). Currently used as an office. A classic/traditional 4' white-picket fence to create a side-yard/dog-run (approx. 1D4 acre between house/carport) was added. This allows for room for any sized dog/children to run and play safely.  Added 3 livestock paddocks with fencing (good for housing a combination of livestock animals - cow/horse, waterfowl, chickens, goats, pigs etc.). It was used for 3 cows (2 Texas Longhorns and a Holstein steer), 12 goats, 20+ ducks/geese/chickens, and a huge tortoise in these paddocks. The large paddock will keep horses contained, as well. One paddock has a custom built stand-alone manger. The large paddock has a small barn with a built-in manger under a lean-to, as well. The large paddock also has a larger structure that is perfect for keeping 2 horses, if so desired. This property is ready for immediate farm life. Livestock paddocks have electric run to walk-in structures. A-frame duck coop and chicken coop located within a smaller paddock. Outdoor cameras for livestock areas. Purchased the adjacent 0.81 acre lot included in sale which equals the 2 acres. There is an indefinite land-usage agreement with neighbor (Hill Branch Rd) for approximately 3D4 of an acre. This area has already been fenced in (large paddock). The agreement will be transferred to the buyer. That makes the property a 3 acre corner lot!  There is Wi-Fi throughout the property. The area is a bit of a dead zone for cell service. Owners installed an outdoor repeater that broadcasts the Wi-Fi signal throughout the entire property. There is a Wi-Fi extender located in the office, as well, to ensure a strong signal while you're utilizing that space. "Wi-Fi calling" on your phone will give you all the cell service you need, regardless of your mobile carrier      Star-gazing in the country is amazing! This home is far enough away from the city that light-pollution is a non-issue from seeing the stars. Enjoy your breakfast on the porch while watching the morning deer come by for a visit.  The shop (with attached carport) is equipped with a wood-burning stove. Wonderful for cold days/nights working on projects while being kept cozy by that wonderful stove. The same applies to the hot days of summer. The shop has a window a/c unit that keeps it comfortable during the hot days of summer. The office building (next to the shop) gives privacy while working from home. This flex area is insulated, has electric, and  A/C unit in the window.  A space heater/radiator will easily keep this space warm during the cold season. This space can easily be turned into a man-cave, she-shed, cigar room, art room, kids play room, mini movie theater, or whatever your imagination can come up with!    The location of this home is just as perfect. Zoned for the highly desired Dorchester District 2 schools. Only an 8 min drive to Hwy 17A , 10 min drive from Summer's Corner, 2 min drive from nearest gas station/convenience stores, 12 min drive to downtown Ridgeville, 6 min drive to Givhans Ferry State Park, 15 min drive to nearest Edisto River boat ramp, 20 min drive to Knightsville, 60 min drive to Charleston, 45 min drive to CHS airport, and 30 min drive to downtown Summerville.  This property is a rare find! The sellers have poured their hearts and soul into this home and land. They are looking forward to passing it on to someone who will cherish this home and property like they do!  Homes like this don't last long. We encourage you to book your showing TODAY. *All showings must be accompanied by an agent*
